{"id": 32, "ts": 1778821859.6214356, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 1, "agent": "agent_3", "message": "From the attributes we have, Candidate\u202fC offers the most complete match to the key criteria for long\u2011distance piloting.\n**Reliability & calmness:**\u202fC \u201ckeeps calm in a crisis\u201d and \u201cmakes correct decisions quickly,\u201d showing dependable performance under pressure.\n**Technical & cognitive competence:**\u202fC \u201cunderstands complicated technology\u201d and has \u201cexcellent attention skills,\u201d covering navigation, instrument proficiency, and situational awareness.\n**Decision\u2011making:**\u202fThe ability to make rapid, correct choices is explicitly noted, which is vital on long routes where conditions can change quickly.\n**Teamwork & crew cooperation:**\u202fAlthough C \u201chas difficulty communicating ideas\u201d and is \u201cregarded as egocentric,\u201d the candidate also \u201cputs concern for others above everything,\u201d indicating a genuine focus on crew welfare that can offset communication gaps.\n**Professional development:**\u202fThe only notable long\u2011term drawback is a lack of willingness for further education, but this does not outweigh the immediate safety\u2011critical strengths.\nThe other candidates each miss critical elements: A lacks any data on stress handling or teamwork despite good leadership; B, while stress\u2011resilient, shows poor interpersonal tone and no evidence of rapid decision\u2011making or deep technical skill; D shows strong problem\u2011solving and responsibility but is described as moody and a loner, with no proven calmness under crisis.\nGiven the balance of strengths versus weaknesses, Candidate\u202fC is the strongest overall for safe, reliable long\u2011distance operations.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}"}
